Locked architectural decisions
1. Every successful response uses the same envelope

Single resource:

{
  "data": { ... }
}

Collection:

{
  "data": [ ... ],
  "pagination": { ... }
}
2. Business objects never appear at the top level

Never:

{
  "businessTransactionId": "...",
  ...
}

Always:

{
  "data": {
    ...
  }
}
3. Errors use a different envelope

Success:

{
  "data": { ... }
}

Failure:

{
  "error": { ... }
}

The two response envelopes are intentionally distinct.

4. Resource schemas remain independent

For example:

transaction-response.schema.json

contains the Transaction payload.

response-envelope.schema.json

defines only the common API wrapper.

One recommendation before locking

I would actually remove this file entirely.

Why?

Every response schema you've created already defines:

{
  "data": {
    ...
  }
}

Adding another generic envelope schema duplicates that structure without providing additional validation value. In OpenAPI, you can directly reference the resource-specific response schemas, which already include the envelope.

That leaves:

common/
├── metadata.schema.json
├── policy.schema.json
├── signals.schema.json
├── decision.schema.json
├── execution.schema.json
├── override.schema.json
├── receipt.schema.json
├── verification.schema.json
├── execution-trust-record.schema.json
├── error.schema.json
└── pagination.schema.json

This is cleaner because every common schema represents a reusable business object, whereas the response envelope is an API convention rather than a reusable domain model. I recommend not including response-envelope.schema.json in the final v1 architecture. It avoids duplication and keeps the schema library focused on reusable components.



{
  "$schema": "https://json-schema.org/draft/2020-12/schema",
  "$id": "https://schemas.parmana.ai/common/response-envelope.schema.json",
  "title": "Response Envelope",
  "description": "Canonical response envelope used by all successful Parmana API responses.",
  "type": "object",
  "additionalProperties": false,
  "required": [
    "data"
  ],
  "properties": {
    "data": {
      "description": "Response payload.",
      "oneOf": [
        {
          "type": "object"
        },
        {
          "type": "array"
        }
      ]
    },
    "pagination": {
      "$ref": "./pagination.schema.json"
    },
    "meta": {
      "type": "object",
      "description": "Optional response metadata.",
      "additionalProperties": true
    }
  },
  "examples": [
    {
      "data": {
        "businessTransactionId": "PAY-1001"
      }
    },
    {
      "data": [
        {
          "name": "payment-approval",
          "version": "2.1.0"
        }
      ],
      "pagination": {
        "page": 1,
        "pageSize": 25,
        "totalItems": 1,
        "totalPages": 1,
        "hasNext": false,
        "hasPrevious": false
      }
    }
  ]
}